  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Human Resource Generalist",
  "description": "<p>Roles & Responsibilities</p><p>The HR Generalist is responsible for managing the <strong>full spectrum of HR operations</strong> in a licensed security company, ensuring <strong>regulatory compliance, manpower readiness, and daily operational support</strong>.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Handle end-to-end HR functions including recruitment, onboarding, deployment, and offboarding of security personnel</p></li><li><p><strong>Answer and manage all incoming office calls</strong>, including calls from security officers, clients, sites, and authorities</p></li><li><p>Act as primary HR contact for security officers regarding attendance, leave, deployment issues, and HR matters</p></li><li><p>Prepare and maintain employment contracts, confirmation letters, disciplinary letters, and HR documentation</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate and up-to-date employee records, HR trackers, and personnel files</p></li></ul><p><strong>Security Industry & PRD Compliance:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Ensure compliance with <strong>PRD requirements</strong> for licensed security operations</p></li><li><p>Track security officer licensing, training validity, and renewal timelines</p></li><li><p>Prepare documentation and support <strong>PRD inspections, audits, and checks</strong></p></li><li><p>Liaise with PRD, MOM, training providers, and relevant agencies as required</p></li><li><p>Support Work Permit applications, renewals, cancellations, and MOM submissions</p></li></ul><p><strong>Operational & Payroll Support:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Coordinate closely with Operations team on manpower deployment and scheduling</p></li><li><p>Verify attendance, overtime, relief deployment, and absenteeism records</p></li><li><p>Prepare accurate payroll inputs and support payroll processing</p></li><li><p>Monitor leave, medical certificates, and disciplinary follow-ups</p></li></ul><p><strong>Administrative & Reporting Duties:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prepare HR reports for management and compliance purposes</p></li><li><p>Draft internal memos, official correspondence, and regulatory submissions</p></li><li><p>Support management in improving HR processes and SOPs<br /></p></li></ul><h3>Requirements:</h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Human Resource Management or related field</p></li><li><p>Able to manage high call volume and operational issues calmly</p></li><li><p>Firm, organized, and able to handle sensitive matters professionally</p></li></ul>",
